Note for XTCAV stability (CATER 155434)
text: We've been working with Shantha and the timing team to understand an instability in the phase reference. The reference was changed during the PAMM, and isn't clear it's better. The signal is found on the third PAD, XTCAV LLRF panel -> PAD 3 -> CH3. Observation before last PAMM was roughly diurnally, the reference had a period where the phase would jump around by 90 deg, causing many BCS faults (you go on crest and deflect to the wall randomly). Then it would quiet down and settle on the "other" 90 deg off phase. This repeated ~12H later returning to the original phase. Checking the timing now, it seems okay. In the history, there was one rash of phase reference instability since the PAMM. Phase reference currently reads about -90 deg. If it goes unstable the cavity won't be usable until it stops. If it jumps then is left misphased, the usual XTCAV ACC phase offset on PAD 1 will need adjusting to get on the correct zero crossing (larger PAD phase = BPM reading goes up). Any suspicious behavior, please log or note on CATER.
